      <h1 class='title'>Indirect Tax Revenues</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 27 November 2002 vol 395 c30WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_30ws' title='Col. 30WS &mdash; HC Deb 27 November 2002 vol 395 c30WS' name='column_30ws' href='#column_30ws' rel='bookmark'>30WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0395P2_20021127_CWS_21'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-john-healey' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0395P2_20021127_CWS_21' title='Link to this speech by Mr John Healey' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-john-healey" title="Mr John Healey">The Economic Secretary to the Treasury (John Healey)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para">The Government's latest estimates of the revenue losses affecting VAT, tobacco duty and other indirect taxes, and the supporting methodologies, are set out in documents published today by HM Customs and Excise entitled 'Protecting Indirect Tax Revenues' and 'Measuring Indirect Tax Losses'. Both documents are available in the Libraries of both Houses.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
